      "content": "For high-level women executive roles, hairstyles should be uniform, universally appropriate, and meticulously maintained to signal competence and authority. Recommended options include a voluminous center part with tightly controlled flying hairs, a sleek low bun that keeps hair far away from the face, or a sharp side-swept style that frames features without distraction. The key is avoiding overly styled, textured, or \"laid-back\" looks that may unintentionally soften their perceived leadership status. Prioritize cuts and styles that remain clean, sharp, and cohesive even during movement to ensure a polished, intentional image throughout any boardroom interaction.",
